title: BREAKING: Police Shoot Woman In North Center
text:
BREAKING: Police Shoot Woman In North Center February 10, 2017 6:38 PM Police at Irving Park and Western. (CBS) 
(CBS) — Chicago police have shot a woman in the North Center neighborhood. 
The incident occurred at Iriving Park Road and Western Avenue around 6 p.m. 
Chicago police spokesperson Anthony Guglielmi confirms there was a police-involved shooting in which a female subject was hit. No officers were injured, he said on Twitter. Police involved shooting – 3944 N WESTERN. Female offender shot. No injuries to officers, PIO en route. 
— Anthony Guglielmi (@AJGuglielmi) February 11, 2017 
Check back for details.
